# Code signing for Windows installer (Authenticode)
# Copy to signing.env and fill in — NEVER commit signing.env or .pfx files to git.
#
# 1. Purchase a Windows code signing certificate (Standard or EV) from:
#    - DigiCert, Sectigo, SSL.com, or Microsoft Azure Trusted Signing
# 2. Export as .pfx (includes private key) from the CA portal or cert manager.
# 3. Set paths below, then run: build-installer.bat

# Path to your .pfx file OR base64-encoded pfx (electron-builder accepts both)
WIN_CSC_LINK=C:\certs\business-one-code-sign.pfx
CSC_KEY_PASSWORD=your-pfx-password

# Optional — shown in SmartScreen / certificate details
# CSC_NAME=Business One LLC
